des: "A traditional Filipino coconut milk-based dessert with my own personal modifications to make it quick, easy, and palatable to even the most wary and picky eaters. Serve warm in bowls."
ins: Pour coconut milk into a saucepan over low heat. Simmer, covered, until gently bubbling, 5 to 10 minutes. Stir in sugar until dissolved. Add plantain bananas and tapioca pearls. Simmer until tapioca and plantains soften, 25 to 30 minutes. Stir in yams and jackfruit.
